:::summary
The Protestant Reformation was one of the most consequential events in Western history — a 16th-century religious revolution that permanently split Western Christianity into Catholic and Protestant branches, reshaped European politics, culture, and society, and prepared the ground for both the Enlightenment and the religious pluralism in which the Restoration of the gospel could eventually occur. From a Latter-day Saint perspective, the Reformation was a vital step in God's preparation of the world for the Restoration.
:::

